<body>
  <h1>Exploring the WordPress Dashboard</h1>

  <p class="meta">J Hill</p>

  <p class="meta">October 25, 2025</p>

  <table aria-label="WordPress dashboard sections and purposes">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Section</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Posts</td><td>Manage blog posts: create, edit, categorize with categories and tags, and control publish status (draft, scheduled, published). Useful for time-ordered content and blog/news updates.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Media</td><td>Library for uploaded files (images, video, audio, documents). Upload, edit, and reuse media files; add alt text and basic metadata for accessibility and SEO.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Pages</td><td>Create and manage static pages (e.g., About, Contact). Pages are for timeless content and hierarchical structure (parent/child pages).</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Comments</td><td>Moderate visitor comments: approve, reply, mark as spam, or delete. Manage discussion settings and monitor engagement on posts/pages.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Appearance</td><td>Control site look and layout: themes, widgets, menus, and (depending on theme) site editor / template parts. Customize site identity (logo, colors) and visual presentation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Plugins</td><td>Install, activate, deactivate, and configure plugins that extend site functionality (SEO, caching, forms, security). Manage plugin updates and settings.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Users</td><td>Manage site users and roles (Administrator, Editor, Author, Contributor, Subscriber). Add or remove users and set permissions for content access and administration.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Tools</td><td>Access import/export tools, site health and other administrative utilities. Helpful for migrating content, checking diagnostics, and performing maintenance tasks.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Settings</td><td>Global configuration for the site: general site title/timezone, writing/reading options, discussion, media sizes, permalinks and privacy settings. Central place for baseline behavior.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</body>
</html>
